  fiTitle: "Kyynelist\xE4 syntyneet"
  fiDesc: Lasi
  fiIntroText: "Niit\xE4 on harva n\xE4hnyt. Ne lentelev\xE4t sateenkaaren v\xE4risiss\xE4
    spektreiss\xE4, kun valo leikkaa lasia. Salamannopeasti, ne ovat siin\xE4 ja
    sitten poissa. Ne ovat yht\xE4 hauraita kuin ohut lasi. Yht\xE4 l\xE4pikuultavia.\r\n\r\nKerrotaan,
    ett\xE4 ne ovat syntyneet lasinpuhaltajien kyynelist\xE4, kun ne ovat putoilleet
    lasinsirpaleisiin. Niist\xE4 kyyneleist\xE4, joita on syntynyt, kun olet niin
    l\xE4hell\xE4 t\xE4ydellist\xE4 ty\xF6t\xE4 ja sitten se kuitenkin s\xE4rkyy.
    Tai menett\xE4\xE4 ainutlaatuisen muotonsa. Tai ilon kyynelist\xE4, kun tulos
    on t\xE4ydellinen, juuri sellainen, jonka lasinpuhaltaja sielussaan n\xE4ki.
    \r\n\r\nLasikeijut eiv\xE4t el\xE4 kauaa, kaikilla niill\xE4 on syntyess\xE4\xE4n
    lasisairaus, mutta ne syntyv\xE4t uudelleen, koska lasinpuhaltaja voi puhaltaa
    niihin pienen lasisyd\xE4men, piskuisen pisaran el\xE4m\xE4\xE4 yll\xE4pit\xE4m\xE4\xE4n.
    \r\n\r\nN\xE4kev\xE4tk\xF6 vain lasinpuhaltajat lasikeijuja? Ei, muutkin voivat
    n\xE4hd\xE4 niit\xE4, jos\u2026 L\xE4hdet\xE4\xE4n etsim\xE4\xE4n.\r"
  fiOutroText: "Lasia on monenlaista, niin on lasikeijujakin. Samassa esineess\xE4kin
    toinen sen n\xE4kee ja toinen ei.\r\nKeijut eiv\xE4t siit\xE4 kyll\xE4 suutu,
    he ovat siihen tottuneita. Ett\xE4 toisen kaunis ei olekaan kaikkien kaunis.\r\nEik\xE4
    keijuja ihan kaikissa lasiesineiss\xE4 olekaan. \r\n\r\nLasikeijut syntyv\xE4t
    vain silloin, kun itse tekij\xE4 n\xE4kee luomisty\xF6ns\xE4 kauneuden. Sen,
    mit\xE4 on tavoitellut. Se on hetki, jossa ihmeit\xE4 tapahtuu. \r\n\r\nJoskus
    keijut heitt\xE4ytyv\xE4t leikkisiksi. Ne laskevat liukum\xE4ke\xE4 auringons\xE4teiss\xE4,
    spektrin eri raidoissa. Ne pelottelevat toisiaan kuperien lasien pinnoilla n\xE4ytt\xE4en
    j\xE4ttil\xE4iskokoisilta tai vaihtavat v\xE4ri\xE4 sukeltaen eriv\xE4riseen
    lasiin. \r\n\r\nLasikeijut el\xE4v\xE4t ihmisten keskuudessa niin kauan kuin
    joku n\xE4kee esineen kauneuden. Niin kauan lasikeijulla on koti, mutta koditonna
    se palaa keijujen maahan. Se tulee luoksemme uudelleen, kun jossain joku puhaltaa
    uuden luomuksen ja n\xE4kee j\xE4lleen lasin kauneuden. \r\n\r\nLasikeiju on
    kuin lasi, niin haurasta ja niin kest\xE4v\xE4\xE4, niin helposti s\xE4rkyv\xE4\xE4
    ja niin ikuista.  Riippuen t\xE4ysin siit\xE4, miten sit\xE4 kohdellaan.\r"
  enTitle: Born from tears
  enDesc: Glass
  enIntroText: "Only the lucky few have seen them. They fly around in spectres in
    the colours of the rainbow when the light passes through glass. They are here
    at lightning speed, and then they are gone. They are fragile and as thin as glass,
    and just as transparent.\r\n\r\nThe story goes that they are created as the tears
    of the glass-blowers drop into pieces of broken glass. The tears are shed when
    you are so close to a perfect piece and the lose it, and it shatters or loses
    its unique shape. Or of tears of joy when the item turns out perfect, just like
    the glass-blower\u2019s soul predicted. \r\n\r\nGlass fairies only live for a
    moment as they are all born with glass disease, but they are born again as a
    glassblower can blow a small glass heart for them, a tiny bubble of life to sustain
    them. \r\n\r\nAre the glassblowers the only ones who can see the glass fairies?
    No, others can too if... Let\u2019s find out.\r"
  enOutroText: "Glass comes in many forms, and so do glass fairies. Even if someone
    can see them in a certain object, someone else might not.\r\nThe fairies do not
    care, they are used to the fact that what is beautiful to someone is not necessarily
    beautiful to everyone else.\r\nAnd fairies do not occupy all glass objects, either.
    \r\n\r\nGlass fairies are only born when the glassblower sees the beauty of their
    creation, sees what they were trying to achieve. It is in that moment when miracles
    happen. \r\n\r\nSometimes the fairies like to play. They slide down sunrays,
    having fun in the stripes of the spectre. They playfully scare each other on
    the convex surfaces of the glass objects so that they look gigantic or change
    colours by diving into multicoloured glass. \r\n\r\nGlass fairies live among
    people as long as someone sees the beauty of the object. That is how long the
    fairy will have a home; without a home, she has to return to Fairy Land. She
    will return to us when someone blows a new glass object and sees its beauty.
    \r\n\r\nThe glass fairy is as fragile and durable as glass, so easy to break
    and just as eternal. Everything depends on how it is treated.\r"
